# KiCad CLI on Windows

When the workspace OS is Windows/win32:

- Use Git Bash for KiCad CLI commands.
- KiCad CLI is available as KiCad 10.0.1 on PATH inside Git Bash.
- Prefer running KiCad CLI commands via:
  `& "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\bash.exe" -lc 'kicad-cli version'`
- In Git Bash, `kicad-cli` is on PATH from `/c/Program Files/KiCad/10.0/bin`.
- Do not assume WSL2 is available; avoid WSL2-only commands for this project.

On non-Windows environments, use the native shell and native `kicad-cli`.
